dcterms:description: A framework designed to provide homogeneous, unified, end-to-end QoS management over heterogeneous access technologies, incorporating adaptive resource control and context-aware functionalities.
dcterms:title: CNQF (Converged Networks QoS Management Framework)

dcterms:description: An API for managing network devices using SNMP, facilitating measurement and monitoring capabilities.
dcterms:title: SNMP (Simple Network Management Protocol)

dcterms:description: Standard reference for Management Information Base Object Identifiers used in network management.
dcterms:title: RFC 1213 MIB OIDs (Management Information Base Object Identifiers)

dcterms:description: A versatile traffic generator used for generating various types of network traffic for testing and evaluation.
dcterms:title: ntools (Traffic Generator)

dcterms:description: A conceptual framework that utilizes fuzzy logic for adaptive resource allocation and management in network systems.
dcterms:title: Fuzzy Rule Based System (FRB)
